Provenance

The skills, subagent template, ADR conventions, and governance shape in this
scaffold were extracted and generalised from RepoNav
(github.com/Mansour-ElCheikh/Reponav, Apache-2.0). RepoNav remains the
canonical case-study installation; the eval evidence cited in the README is
from RepoNav's eval harness (sweep 2026-05-03-1905-T6L8) and is published,
pinned to the measured RepoNav commit and model snapshot, in a dedicated
evals repository: github.com/Mansour-ElCheikh/evals (Apache-2.0; see
evals/README.md).

---

Third-party attribution

This product ships documents, conventions, shell-script templates, and a
local TypeScript CLI (the governance engine, scaffold wrapper, and three
per-tool emitters). It is not a service, daemon, or SDK: no network calls,
no `import` statements wired into adopters' application code, no runtime
component in production. The TypeScript CLIs have a small set of npm
dependencies (notably `commander`, `js-yaml`); the documents and templates
ship as files only. Emitted adopter artefacts (`.claude/skills/`,
`.cursor/rules/`, `.github/instructions/`, `governance.yaml`, etc.) are
Markdown / YAML / shell only and contain no bundled JavaScript
dependencies. See ADR-0008 for the runtime-language reconciliation.
